						<summary>

						<p>This records an agreement given by five residents of Madanamañjari-chaturvēdimaṅgalam a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēya</hi> village of Nenmali-nāḍu to maintain a perpetual lamp in the temple of Tiruvirāmīśvarattu-Mahādēva for 24 <hi rend="italic">kāśu</hi> received by them from <hi rend="bold">Tirumañjuṇappitta</hi> a servant of the temple. This is also probably a record of <hi rend="bold">Uttama-Chōḷa.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
